title: Zenith (Grayskul album)
text:
Zenith is a studio album by American hip hop group <a href="Grayskul">Grayskul</a>. It was released on <a href="Fake%20Four%20Inc.">Fake Four Inc.</a> on September 17, 2013.
Critical reception.
Chul Gugich of "<a href="Beats%20Per%20Minute%20%28website%29">Beats Per Minute</a>" gave the album a 73 out of 100, saying, "Grayskul has done its part in keeping Seattle hip hop weird and unpredictable." Kyle Fleck of "<a href="The%20Stranger%20%28newspaper%29">The Stranger</a>" described it as "a sprawling collection of 17 tracks that broadens Grayskul's core aesthetic while maintaining their trademark dark humor and densely packed wordplay, with a diverse set of beats of a quality befitting the upper echelon of the underground." Azaria C. Podplesky of "<a href="Seattle%20Weekly">Seattle Weekly</a>" said, "a variety of lyrical content and futuristic beats keep things interesting."
